Archbishop Emeritus Desmond Tutu has been admitted to hospital for treatment of a "stubborn" infection. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Archbishop Emeritus Desmond Tutu has been admitted to hospital for treatment of a "stubborn" infection. Tutu has been hospitalised several times over the past few years for treatment of a similar condition. READ: Archie meets The Arch Last month the 88-year-old met the Springboks, praising them for their Rugby World Cup victory. The Nobel Peace Prize winner also urged the country to continue building on the momentum brought about by win. His wife, Leah, says the Arch is being treated for a stubborn infection. We spoke to Niclas Kjellström-Matseke, Chairman of the Desmond & Leah Tutu Legacy Foundation. Courtesy #DStv403